00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:41,470
The operation will
take place tomorrow.

253
00:17:55,850 --> 00:17:57,680
Don't you do that to me ever again.

254
00:17:58,970 --> 00:18:03,220
Don't try to cut me off in front
of my patient. - Sir, I was just..

255
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:05,020
When I am saying OT is not available..

256
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:06,180
..it means OT is not available.

257
00:18:06,270 --> 00:18:08,470
Sir, I was informed that the
surgery has been cancelled.

258
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:11,270
So I thought of informing you.
- Dr. Romesh.

259
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:14,310
I know the surgery has been cancelled.

260
00:18:15,470 --> 00:18:16,930
I know OT is available.

261
00:18:17,020 --> 00:18:19,140
But the kid will stay
here tonight. You know why?

262
00:18:20,180 --> 00:18:21,350
Because I am saying it.

263
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:23,220
Simple.

264
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:26,560
If you want to be a
successful doctor, remember that..

265
00:18:26,850 --> 00:18:28,470
..along with being a profession,
it's a business too.

266
00:18:29,430 --> 00:18:30,560
You need money for treatment.

267
00:18:30,890 --> 00:18:33,100
These modern machines,
medicines, staff..

268
00:18:33,180 --> 00:18:34,270
..hasn't come free.

269
00:18:34,350 --> 00:18:35,430
It has been bought with money.

270
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:38,180
To run the hospital you need
money and not just goodness.

271
00:18:40,850 --> 00:18:42,470
Without money, there
will be no hospitals.

272
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,060
Without hospital, no treatment.

273
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:46,310
If you sympathize
with them, tell them..

274
00:18:46,390 --> 00:18:49,430
..to stop going to expensive
beauty parlors for a month.

275
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:50,680
They will save money.

276
00:18:52,390 --> 00:18:54,100
If she can't even do
this for her son..

277
00:18:54,430 --> 00:18:55,770
..then she shouldn't
expect anything from us.

278
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:59,930
One patient's money comes
to another patient's aid.

279
00:19:00,020 --> 00:19:01,350
So they bloody well
pay for each other.

280
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:03,600
Do you understand?
- Yes, sir.

281
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:05,060
Do you understand, Dr. Romesh?

282
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:09,310
I am asking you, Dr. Romesh.
Do you understand?

283
00:19:09,390 --> 00:19:12,810
Sir, we understand. We all understand.

284
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:15,770
What you are saying makes sense.

285
00:19:19,810 --> 00:19:23,310
Try to understand.
Learn something from her.

286
00:19:32,850 --> 00:19:33,970
Take it easy.

287
00:19:41,890 --> 00:19:43,640
Hey, champ. You okay in there?

288
00:19:44,060 --> 00:19:45,970
Yeah. Okay.

289
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:47,850
I am not scared.

290
00:19:48,220 --> 00:19:49,270
Good.

291
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:51,100
Shall I ask you a question?

292
00:19:52,470 --> 00:19:56,470
Sure. - Can people die
during asendipitis operation?

293
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:59,520
Its not asendipitis.
It's appendicitis.

294
00:20:00,310 --> 00:20:02,220
And, no. No one dies
in this operation.

295
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:03,770
They just survive.

296
00:20:04,470 --> 00:20:06,350
And we won't let you die.

297
00:20:06,430 --> 00:20:09,180
Are you sure?
- Very sure.

298
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:21,720
Is it just appendix?
Or any other complication?

299
00:20:22,890 --> 00:20:24,180
Only appendicitis.

300
00:20:26,390 --> 00:20:28,060
But if you and Dr. Asthana want..

301
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:29,850
..we can conduct many more tests.

302
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:32,810
So that this hospital can do business.

303
00:20:33,770 --> 00:20:36,970
Romesh, I was just..
- You understand everything.

304
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:42,140
I am getting bored.

305
00:20:43,140 --> 00:20:44,680
For how long will I have to lie down?

306
00:20:45,220 --> 00:20:46,520
Just 10 minutes more, champ.

307
00:20:51,850 --> 00:20:53,390
Shall I tell you something?

308
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:56,390
But don't tell mom.

309
00:20:57,640 --> 00:21:00,810
Sure. I am an expert
in keeping secrets.

310
00:21:01,470 --> 00:21:06,220
You see, I don't feel
good that I am sick.

311
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:10,020
Because mom is sad because of me.

312
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:12,310
She was already sad.

313
00:21:13,140 --> 00:21:16,220
And...and she is sadder now.

314
00:21:17,270 --> 00:21:18,770
Don't worry. You will be fine.

315
00:21:19,140 --> 00:21:21,220
She thinks I don't know anything.

316
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:23,890
I am a kid.

317
00:21:24,640 --> 00:21:26,020
But I am not a kid.

318
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:29,680
I know papa has left us forever.

319
00:21:32,970 --> 00:21:37,020
I even know that mom
doesn't cry in front of me.

320
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:40,430
She cries alone in her bedroom.

321
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:46,850
Make me alright. I will earn a
lot of money once I grow up.

322
00:21:48,310 --> 00:21:49,600
Only for mom.

323
00:21:50,270 --> 00:21:52,390
I will buy many presents for her.

324
00:21:53,310 --> 00:21:54,930
I will always keep her happy.

325
00:21:56,020 --> 00:21:58,970
I won't leave her like papa.

326
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:17,970
Romesh, it's not fair.

327
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:20,310
You are venting out
Asthana's anger on me.

328
00:22:21,430 --> 00:22:23,850
I was just easing the tension
between Dr. Asthana and you.

329
00:22:23,930 --> 00:22:27,180
That's all. It was really
getting out of control.

330
00:22:28,970 --> 00:22:30,100
Do you know, Riya?

331
00:22:31,100 --> 00:22:35,680
When I was small,
my mother used to tell me..

332
00:22:37,220 --> 00:22:39,220
..when a person's courage wanes..

333
00:22:40,560 --> 00:22:41,770
..he becomes more cunning.

334
00:22:43,810 --> 00:22:45,970
And when I was small,
my mother had also told me.

335
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:48,720
Instead of unnecessary bravery,
it's better to keep quiet.

336
00:22:49,520 --> 00:22:50,770
Fight only when you can fight.

337
00:22:50,850 --> 00:22:52,390
Not when you don't
have the power to fight.

338
00:22:58,520 --> 00:23:00,970
Tomorrow, Dr. Asthana
won't let me come in the OT..

339
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:02,390
..for Ankur's operation.

340
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:07,890
Take care of the kid.

341
00:23:09,770 --> 00:23:10,930
Please.

342
00:23:12,180 --> 00:23:13,270
I will.

343
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:18,140
And now, will you
break your oath of silence?

344
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:30,970
I love you.

345
00:23:31,930 --> 00:23:33,020
That's the problem.

346
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:35,270
I love you too.

347
00:23:54,770 --> 00:23:57,770
Mama...I am hungry.

348
00:23:59,060 --> 00:24:00,600
You can't eat now, Ankur.

349
00:24:01,350 --> 00:24:02,970
Your operation is after an hour, son.

350
00:24:03,310 --> 00:24:04,890
Come on. Be a brave boy.

351
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:06,970
Eat later.

352
00:24:08,310 --> 00:24:09,560
You are mama's brave boy.

353
00:24:10,850 --> 00:24:11,930
Okay?

354
00:24:18,220 --> 00:24:19,890
Good morning, Ankur.
- Hi.

355
00:24:21,430 --> 00:24:23,060
Good morning, ma'am.
- Good morning.

356
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:25,220
Ma'am, this is a list
for the surgical kit.

357
00:24:25,270 --> 00:24:26,930
You have to buy it
from the surgical shop.

358
00:24:27,180 --> 00:24:29,890
The unused items will be returned.

359
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:33,270
Will you get it if I pay you money?

360
00:24:33,430 --> 00:24:35,270
We don't have anyone else here.

361
00:24:36,770 --> 00:24:37,930
I am sorry, ma'am.

362
00:24:38,220 --> 00:24:41,140
Actually, the hospital staff
is not allowed to take money.

363
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:43,680
And I think it won't take you long.

364
00:24:43,770 --> 00:24:46,270
The shop is not crowded in
the morning. That's why.

365
00:24:48,310 --> 00:24:50,220
Bye, Ankur. Thank you, ma'am.
- Bye.

366
00:24:52,970 --> 00:24:54,100
You will be okay?

367
00:24:55,220 --> 00:24:56,770
I will get it and be back soon.

368
00:24:57,560 --> 00:25:01,020
Send your Gina that yap yap thing.

369
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:03,060
Whatsapp, mom.

370
00:25:03,390 --> 00:25:05,310
Whatsapp.

371
00:25:05,390 --> 00:25:06,720
Okay. I got it.

372
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:11,100
Whatsapp.
- Whatsapp.

373
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:18,140
Carefully. Careful. Careful.

374
00:25:19,020 --> 00:25:21,520
You are not scared, are you?
- No, mom.

375
00:25:22,270 --> 00:25:23,930
The doctors will take care of you.

376
00:25:24,390 --> 00:25:26,390
And uncle Ajay will take care of you.

377
00:25:27,310 --> 00:25:30,560
Naughty. - Of course I will.
And that's a promise.

378
00:25:30,850 --> 00:25:32,020
Stop it.

379
00:25:34,220 --> 00:25:36,100
Bye, mom.
- Bye, son.

380
00:25:36,180 --> 00:25:37,350
See you, champ.

381
00:25:47,060 --> 00:25:48,220
Good morning, Ankur.

382
00:25:48,390 --> 00:25:49,680
Your stomach is empty, right?

383
00:25:50,220 --> 00:25:52,100
You didn't eat anything
in the morning, did you?

384
00:25:52,350 --> 00:25:54,100
No.
- Very good.

385
00:25:54,770 --> 00:25:55,890
Nurse, take this.

386
00:25:57,270 --> 00:25:58,430
Nurse.

387
00:26:01,060 --> 00:26:06,430
Actually, when mom went down,
I was very hungry.

388
00:26:07,270 --> 00:26:09,930
So I ate a few biscuits.

389
00:26:11,270 --> 00:26:12,930
Don't tell mom.

390
00:26:13,390 --> 00:26:15,390
Or else she will be very angry.

391
00:26:17,270 --> 00:26:19,180
Excuse me, sir.
- Yes. It's a black diamond, sir..

392
00:26:19,270 --> 00:26:22,060
Sir, the appendicitis
patient Ankur Arora.. - What?

393
00:26:22,140 --> 00:26:23,890
He is not MBM, sir.
- What?

394
00:26:24,430 --> 00:26:26,720
Sir, that patient Ankur Arora..

395
00:26:26,810 --> 00:26:29,680
..ate a few biscuits. Sir,
his stomach is not empty.

396
00:26:29,770 --> 00:26:32,560
I can't postpone the operation
because of a few biscuits, Rosina.

397
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:33,890
There is a queue for operations.

398
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:36,020
But sir, the operation is
scheduled within an hour. - Yes..

399
00:26:37,100 --> 00:26:39,100
So I will use ryles tube.
Why is that used?

400
00:26:39,310 --> 00:26:42,390
Sir, to clear the patient's
stomach before the operation.

401
00:26:42,470 --> 00:26:44,310
Exactly. It will be done. Now go.

402
00:26:44,810 --> 00:26:46,770
Yes. No. My wife is not coming.

403
00:26:46,850 --> 00:26:48,140
You can introduce me to anybody.

404
00:26:48,220 --> 00:26:49,350
Of course.

405
00:26:51,640 --> 00:26:55,020
Okay. Yeah. It's okay. Bye.
- Excuse me, ma'am.

406
00:26:55,850 --> 00:26:58,770
Yes? - Sir, this is
standard disclaimer form.

407
00:26:59,020 --> 00:27:02,020
A routine operation formality.
So ma'am has to sign here.

408
00:27:02,100 --> 00:27:03,310
Just sign here.

409
00:27:09,270 --> 00:27:11,020
We are ready, sir.
- Good.

410
00:27:15,270 --> 00:27:16,430
Is everything okay, sir?

411
00:27:18,270 --> 00:27:20,770
I am forgetting something.

412
00:27:23,140 --> 00:27:24,930
I had to do something. What was that?

413
00:27:27,470 --> 00:27:28,770
Damn! My phone.

414
00:27:29,930 --> 00:27:31,140
Remove it.

415
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:35,020
Switch it off.
- Sir.

416
00:27:36,390 --> 00:27:37,520
Scalpel please.

417
00:27:37,770 --> 00:27:39,180
Dr. Romesh.

418
00:27:40,270 --> 00:27:41,470
What are you doing here?

419
00:27:42,060 --> 00:27:43,390
I thought you would be in the surgery.

420
00:27:43,470 --> 00:27:45,770
No. Actually,
I am just an intern here.

421
00:27:46,060 --> 00:27:47,520
Dr. Asthana is
conducting the operation.

422
00:27:48,390 --> 00:27:50,770
So nothing to worry about.
He is the best.

423
00:28:32,810 --> 00:28:34,180
A good stitch, sir.

424
00:28:34,270 --> 00:28:35,600
Thank you, Dr. Riya.

425
00:28:36,640 --> 00:28:37,850
Thank you very much everybody.

426
00:28:37,930 --> 00:28:39,390
Keep me posted.
- Yes, sir.

427
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:49,850
Doctor.
- Hello.

428
00:28:51,220 --> 00:28:53,350
Ankur?
- Yes. He is alright.

429
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:54,640
He will regain consciousness soon.

430
00:28:55,310 --> 00:28:57,560
Thank you.. - I have got the
email for the Geneva convention.

431
00:28:57,890 --> 00:28:59,680
I will reply in two days.

432
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:11,560
Ankur, show me your tongue.

433
00:29:12,310 --> 00:29:13,560
Show me your tongue.

434
00:29:14,850 --> 00:29:16,060
Yes. Good.

435
00:29:16,770 --> 00:29:18,270
Open your eyes.

436
00:29:18,350 --> 00:29:21,810
Open your eyes. This too. Good boy.

437
00:29:25,100 --> 00:29:26,520
Okay. Fine. Okay.

438
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:29,770
Oh, my God!

439
00:29:31,390 --> 00:29:33,180
He is vomiting. He is aspirating.

440
00:29:33,270 --> 00:29:35,810
Oh, God! Nurse,
suction machine. Quick.

441
00:29:35,890 --> 00:29:37,020
Yes, sir.

442
00:29:41,310 --> 00:29:43,020
Sir, his oxygen
saturation is dropping.

443
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:46,020
Oh, God! Quickly, nurse.

444
00:29:49,930 --> 00:29:52,560
Nurse, call Dr. Asthana immediately.
- Yes, doctor.

445
00:29:54,270 --> 00:29:57,020
Doctor. Dr. Asthana.
- Hold on.

446
00:29:57,520 --> 00:29:58,720
Keep him under observation for two
more days. - Okay, sir. - Doctor.

447
00:29:58,810 --> 00:30:01,930
Appendicitis patient
is aspirating in the OT.

448
00:30:03,270 --> 00:30:05,930
Damn! Ryles tube! Damn!

449
00:30:06,020 --> 00:30:08,220
I cannot see anything.
Give me the tool.

450
00:30:10,350 --> 00:30:11,430
Okay.

451
00:30:11,850 --> 00:30:14,890
Hold it. Oh, no! It is a mess.

452
00:30:15,560 --> 00:30:18,100
What's going on?
- He aspirated, doctor.

453
00:30:18,310 --> 00:30:20,930
Why didn't anyone tell me that he
ate something before the operation?

454
00:30:22,810 --> 00:30:25,640
Intubator. - There is a lot of vomit.
Let me clean this first.

455
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:27,520
Sir, oxygen saturation is down to 60.

456
00:30:30,220 --> 00:30:32,270
Just intubate him.
The oxygen is not reaching his brain.

457
00:30:32,350 --> 00:30:33,810
Nurse, quick. Get the tube.

458
00:30:34,180 --> 00:30:36,470
Give me the tube.
- Sir, oxygen saturation is down to 50.

459
00:30:37,390 --> 00:30:39,560
I cannot see anything.
There is food all over.

460
00:30:39,770 --> 00:30:41,270
You are not doing this
for the first time, doctor.

461
00:30:41,350 --> 00:30:42,430
You have done this a thousand times.

462
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:43,600
Now don't disappoint me. Please.

463
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,430
I cannot see any damn thing, doctor.

464
00:30:45,810 --> 00:30:47,470
Damn! Telescope.

465
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:49,770
Ventilator.

466
00:30:49,850 --> 00:30:51,220
Saturation is down.

467
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:52,890
It's in. It's in.

468
00:30:53,770 --> 00:30:55,180
The tube is in esophagus
and not in the trachea.

469
00:30:55,270 --> 00:30:56,850
There is no way,
doctor. Come on. Take it out.

470
00:30:57,270 --> 00:30:59,810
Oh, God!
- Saturation down to 35.

471
00:31:00,310 --> 00:31:01,390
It's in the trachea now.

472
00:31:02,390 --> 00:31:03,890
Are you sure?
- Yes, sir.

473
00:31:11,140 --> 00:31:12,310
His reading, Dr. Riya?

474
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:14,430
Saturation is 110. Improving.

475
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:18,720
It's going up, sir.

476
00:31:28,270 --> 00:31:30,890
Just check him please.
- What?

477
00:31:31,020 --> 00:31:32,100
Just check the boy.

478
00:31:35,680 --> 00:31:36,770
Ankur.

479
00:31:37,350 --> 00:31:39,140
Ankur, open your eyes.

480
00:31:39,770 --> 00:31:43,600
Ankur. Ankur, can you hear me?
Open your eyes, Ankur.

481
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:46,270
Ankur, open your eyes. Open your eyes.

482
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:48,970
Ankur, can you hear me? Ankur,
open your eyes.

483
00:31:49,100 --> 00:31:51,270
Ankur, open your eyes. Ankur. Ankur.

484
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:53,720
He is not responding.

485
00:31:55,930 --> 00:31:57,350
We have lost him.
- What?

486
00:31:58,140 --> 00:31:59,180
He is in hypoxia.

487
00:32:01,390 --> 00:32:02,470
He is in coma?

488
00:32:13,270 --> 00:32:14,350
I messed up.

489
00:32:16,850 --> 00:32:20,720
For the first time in
life...I have messed up.

490
00:32:22,850 --> 00:32:23,970
What happened, doctor?

491
00:32:28,430 --> 00:32:30,310
Rosina told me the
patient...ate a few biscuits..

492
00:32:32,430 --> 00:32:34,390
..before the operation.

493
00:32:35,390 --> 00:32:36,520
What!

494
00:32:38,180 --> 00:32:39,720
I had to use Ryle's tube.

495
00:32:43,470 --> 00:32:44,520
I forgot.

496
00:32:48,430 --> 00:32:49,520
Damn!

497
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:04,220
Look...we are all doctors.

498
00:33:04,310 --> 00:33:08,020
So...doctors support each other.

499
00:33:12,390 --> 00:33:16,430
Whatever happened in the
operation theatre will remain here.

500
00:33:16,890 --> 00:33:22,470
But, doctor..
- It's not just...my mistake...doctor.

501
00:33:23,930 --> 00:33:25,140
You should have also checked.

502
00:33:25,270 --> 00:33:27,390
But..
- Okay. Okay.

503
00:33:28,140 --> 00:33:32,270
Whatever
happened...won't be disclosed.

504
00:33:33,310 --> 00:33:34,310
Is that clear?

505
00:33:35,430 --> 00:33:37,770
But Dr. Asthana, if someone asks us..

506
00:33:38,020 --> 00:33:39,560
..how did the child slip into coma..

507
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:42,220
..why have we kept him on ventilator,
what will we say?

508
00:33:42,310 --> 00:33:47,770
Yes. So...we will say
postoperative atelectasis.

509
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:50,890
